details.description:
Sunflower Club is a Cafe and Outreach. We have fresh Belgian waffles, gourmet coffees, teas and locally made baked goods.
11eleven Wellness Bakery is stocking Fresh Artisan delights!
We are dedicated Gluten Free.
You do not have to be a club member to dine in the Cafe.
You may also enjoy paintings and handmade crafts by local artists.
Membership dues and donations fund our outreach programs.

We also have property in Midland, NC called At Kairos. It's a working farm property for education space, wellness retreats and other events that fund our ministry.

Both locations are available to rent.
Contact membership@sunflowerClub.org for info.

I don't live in the area but if I did I would definitely make it a regular stop.

reviews_data.review_text:
Finally, a place dedicated to being as allergen-friendly as possible! All the baked goods and waffles are GF (and taste amazing - in Mint Hill! Even my family, who isn't GF, loved everything they had)...and vegan options (which tastes good!) are available for cheese as well as coffee! Artisen Gelato (DF, vegan from Matthews) is also available here! Yum!

Love the ambiance and way space is sought to be utilized. Very clean, as well! Local artists work available to enjoy and even purchase, as well as great local finds.

Love the focus of this small cafe, and owner's vision. It carries a big impact! I'm eager to make this little spot a regular for our family.

FDA “Refrigerate or freeze meat, poultry, eggs, seafood, and other perishables within 2 hours of cooking or purchasing.”
The chicken was just delivered and out long enough to individually wrap and marinate. That allows for less of a chance to contaminate surfaces when it’s ordered and other food is being made. Lucky for me the FDA gives 2 hours to get that done. 😉

Finally, a place dedicated to being as allergen-friendly as possible! All the baked goods and waffles are GF (and taste amazing - in Mint Hill! Artisen Gelato (DF, vegan from Matthews) is also available here! Yum!

Love the ambiance and way space is sought to be utilized. Very clean, as well! Local artists work available to enjoy and even purchase, as well as great local finds.

Love the focus of this small cafe, and owner's vision. It carries a big impact! I'm eager to make this little spot a regular for our family.

reviews_data.review_text: They left raw, refrigerated chicken out on the counter for at least 10 minutes. Owner was pretty inattentive in general
reviews_data.owner_answer:
FDA “Refrigerate or freeze meat, poultry, eggs, seafood, and other perishables within 2 hours of cooking or purchasing.”
The chicken was just delivered and out long enough to individually wrap and marinate. That allows for less of a chance to contaminate surfaces when it’s ordered and other food is being made. Lucky for me the FDA gives 2 hours to get that done. 😉

The Sunflower Cafe never fails to deliver fresh, delicious and amazing food, every single time I visit! Their creative dishes, like the BLT waffle and seasonal flavored waffles are off the charts delicious! I also love the un-ending variety of coffees and flavors they offer, including my favorite, CBD coffee! It’s just the right amount of energy and chill, in one cup!

raw_data.name: Sunflower Club Cafe & Outreach
raw_data.description:
Sunflower Club is a Cafe and Outreach. We have fresh Belgian waffles, gourmet coffees, teas and locally made baked goods.
11eleven Wellness Bakery is stocking Fresh Artisan delights!
We are dedicated Gluten Free.
You do not have to be a club member to dine in the Cafe.
You may also enjoy paintings and handmade crafts by local artists.
Membership dues and donations fund our outreach programs.

We also have property in Midland, NC called At Kairos. It's a working farm property for education space, wellness retreats and other events that fund our ministry.

Both locations are available to rent.
Contact membership@sunflowerClub.org for info.
